<paragraph id="7CED52860CF22B8659ABABFE3C41D056" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">
The specimens seen are all woodier with more regular vegetative branching than most members of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="F6863D72DE4B0E0C226DF109BC8D43A9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Fleischmannia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Fleischmannia" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="52D51F1E402A6FB0560D6FF978DED48F" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Fleischmannia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This is only Brazilian species known with obviously broadened bases on the pappus bristles. The species is presently known only from Santa Catarina.
</paragraph>
